  "texts": [
    "While the original TinyLlama model displayed competent performance, the integration of symbolic reasoning into the improved model has led to a marked enhancement in producing logically consistent outcomes.",
    "The most pronounced improvements were observed in Analogical Reasoning and Commonsense Reasoning tasks, indicating that the model's ability to navigate complex logical constructs and everyday scenarios has been substantially refined.",
    "These findings underscore the value of hybridizing deep learning with symbolic reasoning, particularly in the domain of logical consistency, and support the hypothesis that such an approach can yield a more nuanced and dependable language model.",
    "C. Rule Adherence Score AssessmentEvaluating the Rule Adherence Score (RAS) is essential to determine how well both the original and improved TinyLlama models can adhere to predefined rules within the context of various tasks.",
    "This metric reflects the models' ability to not only generate plausible responses but also to follow strict logical guidelines and constraints imposed by the symbolic reasoning layer.The results depicted in Figure 4 illustrate that the improved TinyLlama consistently outperforms the original model in terms of RAS for all evaluated tasks."
  ],
